(7379,	3189,	'_resume_content',	'HIGHLIGHTS AND QUALIFICATIONS:\r\n\r\nØ  5+ years Project Management experience in fast-paced environments.\r\n\r\nØ  10+ years of experience meeting deadlines, producing high-quality work.\r\n\r\nØ  5 years working in enterprising, entrepreneurial environments.\r\n\r\nØ  Bachelor’s Degree &amp; Master of Business Administration (MBA).\r\n\r\nØ  Certified Project Management Professional (PMP) and Scrum Master (CSM).\r\n\r\nØ  Excellent written and verbal communications skills, working with diverse populations.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nKEY KNOWLEDGE AND SKILLS\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n§  MS Project Certified\r\n\r\n§  Leadership\r\n\r\n§  Team Management\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n§  MS Office 2010\r\n\r\n§  Change Management\r\n\r\n§  Focused on Results\r\n\r\n§  Planning\r\n\r\n§  Agile/SCRUM\r\n\r\n§  SQL/SharePoint Certified\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nPROFESSIONAL EXPERIENCE\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nProject Manager &amp; Scrum Master (Consultant)                                                                                                                        Dec 2014 - Present\r\n\r\nInterplay Experience Design; Seattle, WA\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nØ  Reduced executive oversight hours by 85%, maintaining 100% goal completion.\r\n\r\nØ  Applied Scrum framework with remote team of three, developing company web presence and platform for social media.\r\n\r\nØ  Developed business requirements and negotiated timelines for completion, satisfying all expectations within given timeframes.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nVendor Relationship Manager (Contract)                                                                                                                                         July – Dec 2014\r\n\r\nGetty Images; Seattle, WA\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nØ  Initiated vendor information management process improvements with a team of fifteen, saving 12% staff time.\r\n\r\nØ  Entrusted to manage challenging worldwide creditor and vendor relationships, ensuring accounts were current.\r\n\r\nØ  Managed project, improving and documenting best practices which created long-term team benefits.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nCredit Analyst (Contract)                                                                                                                                                           Dec 2013 – June 2014\r\n\r\nBECU; Tukwila, WA\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nØ  Championed twelve-person project investigating redesign of paper-intensive data entry process into electronic system using Excel, projected to save up to $240,000 per year.\r\n\r\nØ  Reinitiated sustainability action team, investigating and implementing eco-efficiencies throughout the organization.\r\n\r\nØ  Adhered to all time-lines in completing assignments, producing desired results to satisfy end customers.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nProject Coordinator (Contract)                                                                                                                                                             Jul – Aug 2013\r\n\r\nFred Hutchinson Cancer Research Center; Seattle, WA\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nØ  Reduced researcher time spent searching for files by 92% through digitizing paper records on a team of twenty.\r\n\r\nØ  Increased efficiency by 10% through simplification of data distribution to ancillary services and adjudication teams.\r\n\r\nØ  Quality control of imaged medical records, verifying accuracy and flagging mistakes for reprocessing 100% of time.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nProject Management Consultant                                                                                                                                              Oct 2012 – Dec 2013\r\n\r\nNARAL of Washington; Seattle, WA\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nØ  Designed and implemented small projects for an office of nine workers to reduce IT administrative costs by 43%, including synching IT systems, reorganizing digital files for easy retrieval and documenting office processes for volunteers.\r\n\r\nØ  Negotiated solutions with service providers, generating 75% cost savings for web-hosting budget.\r\n\r\nØ  Saved up to 15 work-hours each week by digitizing paper financial tracking system.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nCoach                                                                                                                                                                                             Apr 2010 – June 2012\r\n\r\nAlere Wellbeing; Seattle, WA\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nØ  Achieved 52.5% project success rate as compared to 47.5% company average.\r\n\r\nØ  Identified opportunities for process improvements and worked with multi-departmental team of eighteen to document and lay groundwork for new efficiencies, using SharePoint.\r\n\r\nØ  Recognized for exceptional stakeholder engagement.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nOperations Consultant (Contract)                                                                                                                                            Feb 2008 – May 2009\r\n\r\nWestwood Mortgage; Seattle, WA\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nØ  Solely responsible for creating online database tracking status of 100-loan pipeline, totaling $15 million in new business.\r\n\r\nØ  Streamlined loan processing procedures to improve efficiency for staff of seven.\r\n\r\nØ  Studied and documented existing practices and designed modifications, saving average of 10% staff time.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nTeam Lead of Onsite Contractors                                                                                                                                              July 2007 – Oct 2008\r\n\r\nLender Processing Services, for IndyMac Bank; Austin, TX\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nØ  Project manager for eight-person team transitioning 100 employees to new online management system, saving 3 weeks of staff implementation time.\r\n\r\nØ  Mastered 7 proprietary systems, providing efficient and effective operational support across all departments.\r\n\r\nØ  Worked collaboratively with team members to accomplish process improvements resulting in 15% time savings.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nEDUCATION &amp; CERTIFICATIONS\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nProject Management Professional Certification (PMP)                                                                                   Project Management Institute\r\n\r\nEarned Dec 2012                                                                                                                                              PMP # 1562297\r\n\r\nAgile Certified Practitioner (ACP)                                                                                                                         Project Management Institute\r\n\r\nEarned July 2015                                                                                                                                              ACP # 1828717\r\n\r\nScrum Master Certification (CSM)                                                                                                                                                    Scrum Alliance\r\n\r\nEarned Feb 2015\r\n\r\nMBA                                                                                                                                               Pinchot University (formerly BGI); Seattle, WA\r\n\r\nEarned May 2012\r\n\r\nBachelor of Arts                                                                                                                                               Lewis &amp; Clark College; Portland, OR\r\n\r\nEarned May 2002'),
