(3210,	1,	'2016-08-31 12:14:09',	'2016-08-31 12:14:09',	'<strong>About The Technical Project Manager at Groundwork Tech:</strong>\r\n\r\nThe Technical Project Manager at Groundwork Tech is responsible for: managing multiple, concurrent small to medium size projects.  Groundwork Tech provides professional who are ideally matched with the client’s specific needs and will deliver solutions per specifications.  The Technical Project Manager is the crucial link between the customer and the other business units and will manage customer expectations, develop risk mitigation strategy, resolve issues, and communicate internally and externally to key stakeholders.\r\n\r\n<strong>About This Position: <a name=\"_Toc403718418\"></a>Objectives</strong>\r\n<strong>Our client is looking to:</strong>\r\nIdentify and implement organizational and operational improvements that will enhance software engineering productivity, security and sustainability. More specifically improve the capability to:\r\n\r\n• Build an infrastructure that has the ability to scale as needed\r\n• Increase security of data flows\r\n• Set up an IT infrastructure with proper tools and process\r\n• Put in engineering practices that will have the ability to be audited and documented\r\n\r\n<strong><a name=\"_Toc403718419\"></a>Scope of Services:</strong>\r\nTo assess current practices, identify improvement opportunities and improvement recommendations to meet the objectives noted above.  Scope of the review will include;\r\n• Virtual interview key user personnel, including members of the executive team and end users, to develop a cohesive view of use patterns and systems coverage of key business requirements, identifying areas for improvement and exploring the growth plans and overall corporate vision.\r\n• Develop and review requirements for the replacement of the current custom platform for the collection, aggregation and reporting of clinical data.\r\n• Review the current technology baseline including architecture, foundational technologies and platforms, and the current roadmap. This will establish the internal environment for the products and technology.\r\n• Virtual interview key members of the technology team / service team to develop a picture of the overall organizational structure, roles and the skills available within the current team, and to address the current and future product development activities.\r\n• Analyze the development methodology as currently implemented and the development tools in place.\r\n• Review controls around production and developer access and the present promote-to production (P2P) processes.\r\n• Review and assess:\r\n• System, database and deployment architecture including design, scalability and ease of integration/support/upgrade.\r\n• Application scalability to meet the demands due to growth in transaction volume, customers, partners and/or vendors specifically looking for current and possible future bottlenecks, and identify possible mitigation actions.\r\n• Product and database integration points both internally and with any 3rd party partners.\r\n\r\n• Analyze the current Azure and other hosting and on site implementations, considering existing requirements as well as projected growth.\r\n• Review disaster recovery and business continuity plans, including back-up and restore tests, and assess their quality and suitability.\r\n• Review sys admin, MS and hosting contracts, services, licenses and costs and assess their suitability.\r\n\r\nDeliverables:\r\n\r\nClient  will:\r\n\r\n• Provide detail challenges and recommendations for improving IT performance, development deployment, functionality and minimizing IT risk using generally accepted IT guidelines\r\n• Document existing IT infrastructure and workflows\r\n• Verification and validation of roles, responsible people, processes and technology.\r\n\r\n<strong>Out of Scope Activities:</strong>\r\n• Any activities not listed above including, but not limited to the following:\r\n• Customer Support organization, process and tools except to the extent they specifically impact engineering workflow\r\n\r\n• Implementation of the recommended improvements. Crosslake will be available to help support implementation as needed however since the improvements have not yet been identified it is out of scope for this SOW.\r\n\r\nAny areas that are not defined as “in scope” are specifically “out of scope.” Items defined in the “out of scope” section are presented for clarity.\r\n\r\nFor further information or consideration, please contact a Groundwork Tech recruiter at the following address <a href=\"mailto:jobs@groundworktech.com\">jobs@groundworktech.com</a>.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;',	'Technical Project Manager',	'',	'publish',	'closed',	'closed',	'',	'technical-project-manager',	'',	'',	'2016-08-31 13:04:16',	'2016-08-31 13:04:16',	'',	0,	'http://gwtweb-migration.azurewebsites.net/?post_type=job_listing&#038;p=3210',	0,	'job_listing',	'',	0),
(3211,	1,	'2016-08-31 12:41:02',	'2016-08-31 12:41:02',	'<strong>About This Position:</strong>\r\n\r\nThe Senior Program Manager Security Operations Center has strong expertise in Managed Security Service Provider (MSSP), network security monitoring and incident response. The SOC Manager will be open minded, bring fresh ideas to the outsourced (MSSP) SOC team and be ready to protect, defend and respond to information security related events. Also, the SOC Manager, will lead key MSSP program elements including the following areas Predictive monitoring, Threat and Vulnerability Management, Threat Hunting and Cyber Security Risk Assessments. The SOC Manager will be responsible for security awareness and enforcement. This will be accomplished by pulling together information from a variety of systems; and normalizing and correlating the information. The SOC provides real-time (or near real-time) detection and reaction services for information security incidents within the company. Decision making is one of the most important traits.\r\n\r\n<strong>Primary Responsibilities:</strong>\r\n\r\n• Perform in-depth network security analysis and work with the SOC analyst team conducting incident response, event analysis and threat intelligence for the corporate enterprise\r\n• Provide both strategic analysis and near real-time auditing, analyzing, investigating, reporting, remediation, coordinating and tracking of security-related activities for the corporate enterprise\r\n• Analyze data and prepare reports that document vulnerabilities from network based attacks and recommends actions to prevent, repair or mitigate these vulnerabilities\r\n• Provide technical mentoring to other team members\r\n• Establish and create standard operating procedures for a variety of computer network defense (CND) related tasks/positions within the team\r\n• Provide technical expertise on post event network security logs and trend analysis\r\n• Review security events that are detrimental to the overall security posture; analyze and detect sophisticated and nuanced attacks and discern false positives and provide results to management\r\n• Perform correlation of events from a variety of network, enterprise and host collection sensors\r\n• Coordinate and liaise with other departments within the company and external auditors with information regarding intrusion events, security incidents, and other threat indications and warnings information\r\n• Demonstrate both technical acumen and critical thinking abilities\r\n• Experience with trouble ticketing and change management tools\r\n• Coordination and escalation of issues to the Incident Response team\r\n• Provide detection and response to security events and incidents within <strong>CUSTOMER</strong> Network\r\n• Web application vulnerability scanning\r\n• Security log management and monitoring\r\n• Intrusion detections and prevention systems operations\r\n• Maintaining information security metrics\r\n\r\n<strong>Required Skills:</strong>\r\n\r\n• Strong knowledge of leading MSSP program\r\n• Security log management\r\n• Strong analytical, documentation, and communication skills\r\n• Strong understanding of IDS &amp; IPS technologies\r\n• Strong understanding of Windows event log analysis\r\n• Experience with enterprise information security data management tools such as ArcSight, Splunk; etc.\r\n• Understanding of network traffic analysis\r\n• 8+ years of applicable experience and a minimum of 5 years of supervisory experience\r\n• Must possess planning, organizational, and motivational skills, able to write clearly and succinctly in technical and non-technical formats.\r\n• Ability to speak both extemporaneously and in formal settings.\r\n• Experience in root cause analysis, industry benchmarking, survey evaluation and data interpretation is required.\r\n• Have the ability to apply logic and reason to solve complex problems.\r\n• Able to infuse innovation and creativity to strategic plans.\r\n• Possess knowledge in the area of emergency/disaster management, physical security, critical incident stress management, risk management and business resiliency\r\n• Familiar with emergency procedure protocols and regulatory interfaces.\r\n• Experience in leading a team.\r\n• Strong analytical, critical thinking and problem solving skills.\r\n• Ability to establish and maintain cross-functional and positive working relationships.\r\n• Proven ability to influence key business partners.\r\n• Ability to build strategic vision and drive organizational change.\r\n• Strong organization and planning skill with the ability to work in and define ambiguity/gray areas.\r\n• Advanced computer skills and proficiency.\r\n• Strong inter-personal and networking skills with a strong ability to work in a team environment.\r\n• Ability to work under stressful and tight deadlines as well as the ability to manage in a fast paced environment.\r\n• Above average computer hardware and software knowledge.\r\n• Excellent verbal and communication skills.\r\n• Ability to multi-ask, discerns patterns in details.\r\n• Think through problems for logical solutions, and remain calm and professional under stress.\r\n• Strong decision making ability during both crisis and non-crisis situations.\r\n• Able to work with highly confidential information.\r\n• Must be able to speak clearly,· give direction, and provide guidance to employees and security staff during emergencies.\r\n• Able to work and communicate effectively with all levels of leadership.\r\n\r\n<strong>Required Experience:</strong>\r\n\r\n• Bachelor’s degree in computer science + or a related discipline\r\n• Five to ten years of experience in the security field highly desirable.\r\n• CISSP, CISM, GIAC certifications highly desirable\r\n\r\nFor further information or consideration, please contact a Groundwork Tech recruiter at the following address <a href=\"mailto:recruiting@groundworktech.com\">recruiting@groundworktech.com</a>.',	'Senior Program Manager, Security Operations',	'',	'publish',	'closed',	'closed',	'',	'senior-program-manager-security-operations-3',	'',	'',	'2016-08-31 13:03:54',	'2016-08-31 13:03:54',	'',	0,	'http://gwtweb-migration.azurewebsites.net/?post_type=job_listing&#038;p=3211',	0,	'job_listing',	'',	0),
