(3213,	1,	'2016-08-31 12:29:50',	'2016-08-31 12:29:50',	'<strong>About This Position:</strong>\r\n\r\nThe Enterprise Security Architect is responsible for analyzing the enterprise\'s information security environment and recommending security measures and technology to safeguard information assets. The architect must develop a comprehensive understanding of the Company platforms and strategies in order to improve overall security posture.\r\nThe Enterprise Security Architect will also provide strategic direction on enterprise security architecture and the implementation of appropriate safeguards and controls. Design, support and problem solve infrastructure security solutions which include both technologies and processes. Assess current and planned applications and systems, identifying security architecture issues and designing solutions for gaps The Enterprise Security Architect demonstrates passion towards Information Security while cultivating company wide security awareness. The Architect also serves as an expert in network, OS, and application development security efforts. The person will prepare preventive and reactive measures, evaluating and implementing enhancements.\r\nThe Architect also updates their job knowledge by tracking and understanding emerging security practices and standards and participating in educational opportunities; The Enterprise Security Architect provides consulting and compliance guidance to project teams and IT security policies, industry regulations, and best practices. Determines security requirements by evaluating business strategies and requirements Assists in the development of estimates for security projects and contributes to defining time tables and project plans.\r\n<strong>Primary Responsibilities</strong>:\r\n\r\n• Plan, design and implement security solutions, tools, and monitoring systems. Review new systems designs and major modifications for security implications prior to implementation.\r\n• Document, analyze, and report on IS business processes to recommend security enhancement and improvements.\r\n•  Identifies, understands and documents extensions to, and variants from, security and architecture standards\r\n• Conduct collaborative meetings between the business units, IT teams and security to further the ongoing development of the information security program. Responsible for organizational communications on security events and updates. Creating reports that identify gaps and remediation recommendations working with business units. Strong communication skills are required in verbal and written form, as well as, advanced skills in Power Point, Excel, Project, Visio, and MS Office, and other communication tools.\r\n• Work closely with compliance and policy analysts to document and manage changes in the environment. Manage security remediation efforts, and conduct investigations followed by recommendation proposals.\r\n• Research and review new and emerging technologies and trends. Document security concerns and send out periodic updates.\r\n• Collaborate with application and system architects to design and develop secure solutions across multiple technologies and platforms.\r\n<strong>Required Skills:</strong>\r\n• Minimum of 4 years of experience as a security architect or senior engineer or developer focusing on security working on substantial projects\r\n• Minimum of 6 years of experience in the securing, development, implementation and maintenance of enterprise-level information security systems across multiple platforms\r\n• Deep architectural knowledge of core information security functions and controls including firewalls, identity and access management, vulnerability management, network security, threat detection/SIEM etc.\r\n• Experienced in designing and implementing security controls.\r\n• Reporting and systems auditing experience required.\r\n• Experience may include creating technical reports, technical white papers, presentation development and delivery and technical training\r\n• Experience making and defending sound technical arguments that incorporate relevant technical and business considerations, and building consensus among stakeholders.\r\n• Experience in developing system security plans.\r\n• Experience in the implementation of audit and security controls, and threat and vulnerability management solutions.\r\n• Experience in server OS, Database, and networking technologies, as well as strong knowledge of the SDLC process. • Bachelor\'s degree.\r\n<strong>Required Experience:</strong>\r\n• Experienced in investigating and resolving information security violations, handling and documenting incidents, researching and deploying new security technologies, participating in security audits, as well as developing and documenting security policies.\r\n• Excellent analytical, problem solving and decision making skills; strong planning and organizing skills\r\n• Current experience leading the security architecture effort for a variety of enterprise-class information security policies, practices, systems and capabilities.\r\n• Broad understanding of IT and Information Security technologies, including technical architectures, testing methodologies, system design, and modeling\r\n• Excellent interpersonal skills, including comprehension, conflict resolution, teamwork and relationship building\r\n• Deep architectural knowledge of core information security functions and controls including firewalls, identity and access management, vulnerability management, network security, threat detection/SIEM.\r\n• CISSP, CISM, GIAC or CISA Certification preferred\r\nFor further information or consideration, please contact Groundwork Tech at the following email address jobs@groundworktech.com or call 425-209-0588.',	'Senior Program Manager, Security Operations',	'',	'publish',	'closed',	'closed',	'',	'senior-program-manager-security-operations-2',	'',	'',	'2016-08-31 13:04:06',	'2016-08-31 13:04:06',	'',	0,	'http://gwtweb-migration.azurewebsites.ne